  "extraction_rules": [
    "STRICT TAXONOMY: Every entity MUST have a path to the TIER 0 ROOT LegalEntity.",
    "DOMAIN EXTRACTION: If the text mentions a broad category (e.g. 'consumer electronics', 'luxury goods', 'athletic footwear'), YOU MUST extract it as a ProductDomain entity.",
    "SERVICE PORTFOLIO: Services (iCloud, Apple Music, Subscriptions) MUST be grouped under a 'Service Portfolio' bridge node.",
    "REVENUE EXTRACTION: If an entity is noted for generating revenue (e.g., 'revenue from iPhone'), YOU MUST create a 'Revenue' entity (type Financial)",
    "STRATEGY EXTRACTION: Themes like 'design focus' or 'user experience' MUST be extracted as Strategy or Capability entities and connected to the Root via HAS_STRATEGY.",
    "NESTING RULE: Products (iPhone, Mac) MUST NOT connect directly to the Root if a ProductDomain or ProductFamily exists. Nest them inside.",
    "BRIDGE NODES: If related products are mentioned but no explicit group name is given, use or CREATE a logical bridge node like 'ProductPortfolio' to group them.",
    "SPINE LINKS: Root -> HAS_PRODUCT_DOMAIN -> Domain -> INCLUDES -> Family -> HAS_PRODUCT_LINE -> Line.",
    "NO ORPHANS: Every node MUST lead back to the ROOT. Prioritize the taxonomic chain over associative links.",
    "EVIDENCE: Every relation MUST have verbatim source_text quote."
  ],
