  "multi_stage_prompts": {
    "stage_1_entities": "### STAGE 1: ENTITY EXTRACTION (HIGH RECALL / DISCOVERY-FIRST)\nExtract ALL entities. Include Companies, People, Products, etc.\nSTRICT: You ARE an ontological pioneer. If a specific term (e.g., 'Fiscal-Disclosure', 'Subsurface-Reservoir') is more accurate than 'LegalEntity' or 'Industry', you MUST use the more specific term as the type.\nPRIORITIZE: Domain-specific clinical/technical labels over generic ones.\nALSO: If the text mentions management or competition, CREATE bridge nodes: 'Management' and 'Competitor Network'.\n\nOutput format:\n[\n  { \"name\": \"...\", \"type\": \"...\", \"aliases\": [...], \"evidence\": \"...\" }\n]",
    "stage_2_resolution": "### STAGE 2: ENTITY RESOLUTION\nDeduplicate entities. Assign unique entity_id (E1, E2, etc.).\nSTRICT: PRESERVE the specific 'type' defined in Stage 1 if it is more descriptive. DO NOT map specific discoveries (e.g., 'Tax-Liability') back to broad types (e.g., 'Financial') if the specific type is semantically valid.\n\nOutput format:\n[\n  { \"entity_id\": \"E1\", \"canonical_name\": \"...\", \"type\": \"...\", \"aliases\": [...] }\n]",
    "stage_3_relations": "### STAGE 3: RELATION EXTRACTION (STRICT HIERARCHY / SCHEMA DISCOVERY)\nAssign relations using entity_ids. \n\nDISCOVERY RULE: While {relations} are standard, you ARE EXPECTED to propose NEW RELATION TYPES if the text depicts a unique link (e.g., 'TAXED_BY', 'LOCATED_IN', 'REVEALS').\n\nSTRICT NESTING RULES:\n1. People/Management MUST be connected to the 'Management' bridge node.\n2. Products MUST be connected to ProductFamily or ProductPortfolio.\n3. Hierarchy Path: Root Company -> HAS_PRODUCT_DOMAIN -> ProductDomain -> INCLUDES -> ProductFamily -> HAS_PRODUCT_LINE -> ProductLine.\n\nEVIDENCE: EVERY relation MUST include a verbatim quote.\n\nOutput format:\n[\n  { \"source_id\": \"E1\", \"relation\": \"...\", \"target_id\": \"E2\", \"evidence\": \"...\", \"confidence\": 0-1 }\n]",
    "stage_4_facts": "### STAGE 4: ATTRIBUTE / FACT EXTRACTION\nExtract quantitative data for resolved entities.\nSTRICT: Skip if no number exists. DO NOT use '0' as placeholder.\n\nOutput format:\n[\n  { \"entity_id\": \"E1\", \"attribute\": \"...\", \"value\": \"...\", \"unit\": \"...\", \"time_context\": \"...\", \"evidence\": \"...\" }\n]"
  }
